    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2e0599de_173ac646",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/testing/state.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 347,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-26T08:43:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure if we want to prepend a prefix for all logs messages, it might be a bit verbose if a test outputs bunch of lines. (it makes perfect sense for error messages since each error message should be one-line and self-contained.) WDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 347,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 347,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "fa60f663400037d82370e9fc71fb89bdef833958",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "28d20c8c_fe698d1b",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/testing/state.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 347,
      "author": {
        "id": 1368736
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-26T23:55:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If there was no error you could not differentiate between the different subtests. \n\nThe best example is one subtest of many failing. Without a logging prefix you can not tell when it started because the previous one did not have an error with a prefix.\n\nWe could add messages when subtests are started/finished, but that will also be verbose. Do you have any other ideas?",
      "parentUuid": "2e0599de_173ac646",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 347,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 347,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "fa60f663400037d82370e9fc71fb89bdef833958",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b61e031b_0742dad4",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/testing/state.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 347,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-27T05:30:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How about printing the test name at the beginning of a subtest? It sounds less verbose than prefixing all log messages.\n\nActually it is a recommended practice to print logs before doing heavy operations. We don\u0027t know if a subtest is heavy or not, but it sounds not too bad.\n\n\u003e When you‘re about to do something that could take a while or even hang, log a message using Log or Logf first. This both lets developers know what’s happening when they run your test interactively and helps when looking at logs to investigate timeout failures.\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/HEAD/docs/writing_tests.md#When-to-log",
      "parentUuid": "28d20c8c_fe698d1b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 347,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 347,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "fa60f663400037d82370e9fc71fb89bdef833958",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
